The shrine was completely destroyed by fire during the {{ill|Tenshō period|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (1573–1592) and again in 1914 (Taishō 3). As a result, old documents detailing its establishment and history were lost, leaving its origins unclear.
The shrine’s chief priest, Yasumi Etō, serves as chairman of the Osaka branch of the {{ill|Nippon Kaigi|ja|日本会議|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and head of the Osaka chapter of the {{ill|Shinto Political Federation|ja|神道政治連盟|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The shrine is adjacent to {{ill|Katayama Park|ja|片山公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nipponkaigi.osaka/?p=831 | title=【Report】Councilors' Meeting at the Osaka Local Assembly | publisher=Nippon Kaigi Osaka | date=2012-04-01 | accessdate=2024-02-27 }}</ref>
== Grounds == * Main Hall - Rebuilt in 1984 (Shōwa 59). * Worship Hall - Rebuilt in 1984 (Shōwa 59). * Shrine Office
=== Auxiliary and Subordinate Shrines === * {{ill|Toyokawa Inari|ja|豊川稲荷|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Shrine * Jūnishi Inari Daimyōjin - Small shrines dedicated to each of the {{ill|Chinese Zodiac|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} animals. * {{ill|Atago Shrine|ja|愛宕社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Kamimusubi|ja|神産巣日神|1=Kamimusubi|lt=Kamimusubi-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Shrine
== Festivals == * Autumn Festival: October 19 (Eve) and October 20 (Main Day)
== Access == * A 7-minute walk from {{ill|Suita Station (JR West)|ja|吹田駅 (JR西日本)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on the {{ill|JR Kyoto Line|ja|JR京都線|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of the {{ill|West Japan Railway Company|ja|西日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * A 9-minute walk from {{ill|Suita Station (Hankyu)|ja|吹田駅 (阪急)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on the {{ill|Hankyu Senri Line|ja|阪急千里線|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
